gomodel:SYNGO_3061  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3: \"Reduced AMPAR-mediated glutamatergic synaptic transmission with aberrant dendritic spine morphology in PSD-Zip70KO mice\"\n\nFig.4: \"Decrease in mature spine synapses and aberrant activation of Rap2 in PSD-Zip70KO neurons\"\n\nFig.6: \"PSD-Zip70 modulates Rap2 activity via SPAR- and PDZ-GEF1\"\n\nFig.7: \"PSD-Zip70 regulates spine morphology via modulation of the Rap2 activity\"\n- \"In contrast, depleting all of the Rap2 subtypes (Rap2a, b, and c) or both PDZ-GEF1 and PDZ-GEF2 could recover the spine-morphology defects of PSD-Zip70KO neurons (Fig. 7d-f).\". Experimental description: - \"Here we generated PSD-Zip70 knock-out (PSD-Zip70KO) mice, ...\"\n- \"Cultured neurons were prepared from mouse embryonic brain on embryonic day 16.5 \"\n- \"The coding regions of mouse PSD-Zip70, Rap2, and rat SPAR were amplified by PCR and subcloned into the highly efficient mammalian expression plasmid pCAGGS. \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3061" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

